txt.en: Not as long-lived as Elves, sturdy as dwarves, or resilient as hobbits, Men are renowned for their courage and resourcefulness.

Not as long-lived as Elves, sturdy as dwarves, or resilient as hobbits, Men are renowned for their courage and ingenuity. They are a strong people, fated to become the dominant people of Middle-earth, though they are also weaker of will and more prone to the temptations and wiles of the Enemy.
